main event: An observation of an unknown object occurred on 8 January 1963 in College Park, Maryland, lasting 3-5 minutes.
interesting points: The object was observed overhead and disappeared over the eastern horizon., The observation involved multiple witnesses, including students at the University of Maryland., The object was observed using 7x50 binoculars., The initial analysis suggested the object could be an aircraft, balloon, or astronomical object., The report noted that there was no conflicting information regarding the analysis of the object.
witness description: A premedical student at the University of Maryland
